  "prompt": "What is the procedure to get an admission at Oxford University?",
  "response": "To get admission to Oxford University, follow these steps:\n\n1. Academic Requirements\n- Excellent academic record\n- High school/secondary school qualifications\n- Strong standardized test scores (A-levels, IB, etc.)\n\n2. Choose Your Course\n- Select from over 350 undergraduate programs\n- Review specific course requirements\n- Ensure you meet subject-specific criteria\n\n3. Application Process\n- Apply through UCAS (Universities and Colleges Admissions Service)\n- Submit online application\n- Pay application fee\n- Write a personal statement\n- Obtain academic references\n\n4. Additional Requirements\n- Some courses require additional tests (e.g., CAT, LNAT, MAT)\n- Submit predicted grades\n- Demonstrate English language proficiency (IELTS/TOEFL)\n\n5. Interview Stage\n- Shortlisted candidates are invited for interviews\n- Interviews assess academic potential and subject knowledge\n- Usually conducted by college faculty\n\n6. College Selection\n- Choose a specific Oxford college or apply open application\n- Each college has unique characteristics and admission criteria\n\n7. Offer and Acceptance\n- Receive conditional offer\n- Meet specified grade requirements\n- Accept offer within given timeframe\n\n8. Visa and Accommodation\n- International students need student visa\n- Arrange university accommodation or private housing\n\nCompetitive process with low acceptance rates (around 20-25%).",
